  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (US)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Regulatory Mechanisms:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting large/suspicious transactions\n- Financial institution compliance requirements\n\n4. Enforcement Agencies:\n- Financial Crime Enforcement Network\n- Internal Revenue Service\n- Department of Justice\n- Financial Intelligence Units\n\n5. Penalties:\n- Significant financial fines\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Potential imprisonment\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities across different jurisdictions and financial sectors.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering legal frameworks?",
